1.Purpose

It is educational to Kids because they will know how to take care of themselves as they are growing to the adult hood, they will know the basics of how to handle themselves. It is also entertaining because will be able to play together as a group with also brings friendships. Kids will have the opportunity to know other kids via Tamagotchi. It also relief stress some kids take that as a form of relaxation.

# General design

I used a dog for my pictures because I did research on what kids love when it comes to pappies and I realized that they love beige dogs because they find them cute, kind, loving, sweet and easy to maintain in terms of taking them to bath and feeding.

# Intuitive design

My application is user friendly, and it shows the heading of the application which is bold for every user to see. It has understandable map-reading, Consistent design with the background color Consistency is key in design elements such as colors, fonts, layout, among others, within the application. Consistency develops a solid user experience. Users will find the interface familiar and comfortable to use. Visual cues, Guide the user through the content with visual cues such as headings, subheadings, and use graphics or images where necessary. This includes clear and succinct headings and subheadings that allow the user to scan for and find specific information regarding the application. The buttons will indicate what the dog will be doing. As you can see with the button on the first page that corresponds with “Start” is large for any user to see and on the second page, the buttons are big enough for the user to see “Play”, Feed” and “Clean”. The background color is much lighter so that the text can be visible to see for users.

# Content prioritization

I made sure that all the necessary buttons and textviews are included for the user to navigate the app easily without having any problems.

# Legible text content

I’ve made my font-size large because some users have problems such as age-Related Macular Degeneration or Diabetic Retinopathy which will be easier for them to see and find where to press it has an emotional impact because kids will fall in love with the application the They can touch the human element, causing users to empathize with the people and events in history. Better learning and suggests that a visual may aid in learning and retention. By adding relevant images to the text, a user is better able to remember the main points presented and therefore better understands the what the dog will be doing in content being viewed.

# Make interface elements clearly visible

My interface has white space which means my variables are not crowded and it will not overwhelm the users on what not to click and what to click.

# Hand position controls

Positioning for thumbs: The main placement of controls must be done in such a way that they remain easily reachable by the thumb. If anything, buttons, and other interactive elements must be closer to the bottom of the screen, where the thumb can comfortably reach without much strain.
